A '''repulsorlift chair''',<ref name="SWE Agruss">{{SWE|characters|keeperagruss|Keeper Agruss}}</ref> also called '''repulsor-chair''',<ref name="SWE Lars">{{SWE|characters|cliegglars|Cliegg Lars}}</ref> a '''hoverchair''',<ref name="TPW">"[[The Perfect Weapon]]"</ref> or a '''hover chair''',<ref name="A Valiant Vow">''[[The High Republic: A Valiant Vow]]''</ref> was a one-being, [[repulsorlift]]-powered floating chair.<ref name="SWE Agruss" /> After losing his right [[Limb|leg]] during a violent encounter with [[Tusken Raider|Sand People]], [[Cliegg Lars]] was forced to use one such device.<ref name="SWE Lars" /> [[Agruss]], an overweight [[Zygerrian]] [[Slavery|slavemaster]], also used a repulsor-chair.<ref name="SWE Agruss" /> The [[Siniteen]] [[Golas Aram]] used a hoverchair on [[Irudiru]] shortly before the [[Liberation of Kashyyyk|liberation]] of [[Kashyyyk]].<ref name="Life Debt">''[[Aftermath: Life Debt]]''</ref>

